               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370508-name-149" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-149" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-149" type="surname" value="CUTHBERT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-149" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE CUTHBERT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a warehouseman, and live in Talbot-court, Gracechurch-street. On the afternoon of the 21st of April I was coming out of the court, and saw the prisoner and another following the prosecutor,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183705080037"></xptr>
               <p>towards London-bridge, through Little East Cheap—I saw the prisoner take from the prosecutor's pocket a yellow silk handkerchief—I went up to him—he came towards me, and I laid hold of his collar—he chucked the handkerchief out of his hand directly he saw me—I dragged him to where he threw the handkerchief, and took it up—I gave it to the policeman—the prisoner told me if I did not let go of him he would <hi rend="italic">job</hi> me in the mouth.</p>
               <p>
